name: Magento SOAP v1.9
description: Magento Commerce is the leading provider of open omnichannel innovation. Our open source digital commerce platform and cloud-based omnichannel solutions empower merchants to integrate digital and physical shopping experiences.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Store URL
configuration.description: The URL of your store (i.e. https://magento.your-site.com)

configuration.name: Session ID
configuration.description: Session ID (default is 1 hour - taken from login)

configuration.name: Username
configuration.description: The Username of the Magento user

configuration.name: Password
configuration.description: The password or API Key of the Magento User

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: XML Parser
configuration.description: Specifies the Cloud Elements XML parser to use - v1 for version 1 - v2 for version 2

configuration.name: Time of Getting Token or Performing Authentication
configuration.description: magentosoapv19 Time of Getting Token or Performing Authentication

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Set time interval for polling application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The resources invoices, shipments and products event response will have an "UNKNOWN" event type because those resources do not return all/any date information in their response. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "contacts": { "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts", “idField”: “user.id”, “datesConfiguration”: { "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at", "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX", “createdDateField”: “user.created_at”, “createdDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX" }, "pageSize": 10000 } }

parameters.name: password
parameters.description: The password - taken from the configuration values

parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, the supported operators are '=', '<', '<=', '>', and '>='. For example, to search by created date, the search expression will be where: created_at>='2013-06-18 14:09:07' .
